{
    "analysis": "From the Executor's summary we know metric/trace/log series and global thresholds (P50/P90/P95) per (cmdb_id,kpi). Many services have metrics (cpu, mem, diskio, socket, workload, latency-50/90) and logs (log.row_count, log.error_count). We must now detect metric anomalies inside the incident window (2024-01-17 03:12:50 to 2024-01-17 03:42:50 UTC) using the previously computed global P95 thresholds (calculated from full series). This will narrow candidate faulty components and KPIs. The next step is to find metrics whose values in the incident window exceed their global P95 (treating high values as anomalies). We will later inspect traces/logs for localization once metric candidates are identified.",
